{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_013UcP7vxRgfbojSTofDPAWU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to generate 10 realistic fake OCR recipe text files with specific patterns and rules. Let me break down the requirements:\n\n1. Save to: tools/title-loop/input/{RECIPE_TITLE}.generated.21.txt\n2. Filename rules:\n   - Use SPACES, not hyphens or underscores\n   - Preserve Polish diacritics (e.g., \"Żurek.generated.21.txt\")\n   - Filename title must match main title in text (case-insensitive OK)\n\n3. Recipe mix: ~60% English, ~40% Polish\n4. Variety: soups, mains, desserts, salads, appetizers, breads, drinks, preserves\n5. Mix of multi-word (2-5) and single-word titles\n\n6. DON'T use these existing recipes (long list provided)\n\n7. Pattern requirements:\n   - 5 files with SPILLOVER: Start with 10-50 lines of corrupted text from PREVIOUS recipe, partial measurements, broken words, garbled temps. Real title appears after garbage. 40-60 lines total.\n   - 3 files with METADATA_PREFIX: Category/serving info before title (e.g., 'Lato | Dania główne', 'DLA 4 OSÓB', 'PRZYGOTOWANIE 10 MIN')\n   - 2 files with SPLIT_TITLE: Recipe title split across 2-4 lines, 1-2 words per line\n\n8. File length: 15-60 lines (spillover should be 40-60)\n\nLet me create 10 diverse recipes:\n\n**Existing recipes to avoid:**\nARAYES SHRAK, Smażona zielona fasolka, CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM, SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK, MIXED SEED CRISPBREAD, LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS, Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce, Faszerowana papryka, OVERNIGHT STRAIGHT PIZZA DOUGH, FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS, KREM SELEROWY Z GORGONZOLA, Roasted Root Vegetable Medley, Pan Seared Scallops, Strawberry Short cake, Tiramisu, Mushroom Risotto, Kopytka z Pieczarkami, Bigos, Spiced Butternut Squash Soup, Herb Marinated Olives, Carrot Ginger Soup, Śledzie w Śmietanie, Kompot Malinowy, Żurek, Thai Green Curry, Lemon Blueberry Cake, Zupka Szczawiowa, Beef Tenderloin with Red Wine, Herb Crusted Lamb Chops, Sernik, Rogaliki Maślane\n\nNow I'll select 10 new recipes that avoid all of these, ensuring good variety across categories and language distribution.\n\n1. Grilled Halibut with Lemon Butter - English, main\n2. Placki Rozankowe - Polish, dessert\n3. Minestrone Soup - English, soup\n4. Sałatka ze Świeżych Warzyw - Polish, salad\n5. Crostini with Ricotta and Fig Jam - English, appetizer\n6. Rosemary Focaccia - English, bread\n7. Kompot Porzeczkowy - Polish, preserve\n8. Crème Brûlée - English, dessert\n9. Żurek Białostocki - Polish, soup\n10. Pumpkin Pie with Spiced Cream - English, dessert\n\nI'm going to generate these recipes now. The halibut dish will have corrupted text mixed in before the actual recipe starts, running about 40-60 lines. The Polish pancakes will follow a similar pattern with spillover corruption. Minestrone will have metadata formatting before the title, and the salad recipe will be cut off mid-way through the initial setup.\n\nThe crostini recipe includes spillover text corruption, while the focaccia has its title split across multiple lines. Kompot Porzeczkowy uses metadata prefix formatting, and crème brûlée also has a split title. For the Polish soup, I'm switching from Żurek Białostocki to Flaki do Potraw since Żurek is already included, and this tripe soup will have spillover corruption. The pumpkin pie concludes the list with a split title format.\n\nActually, I notice Flaki do Potraw already exists in the current list, so I need to find a different Polish soup. Zupa Barszczyku would work as a variation distinct from the existing Barszcz entries, also with spillover corruption.\n\nLet me finalize the recipe list with proper OCR error patterns. For spillover files, I'll introduce artifacts like partial words breaking across lines, corrupted measurements with character substitutions, garbled temperature notations, and garbage text preceding the actual title. For metadata prefix files, I'll incorporate seasonal information. I'll generate these now with the appropriate corruption patterns applied.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":64182,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":64182},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"76e8b81d-7b74-4afe-9627-aa6bd9d1a665","uuid":"7c36d5e1-fd42-4e7a-9f60-04a19d7f9778"}
