{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01TEUuM4bGtknve3SafBpjmN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Cs4rAYRxVCJ9sSvayXtQAH","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Pumpkin Pie with Spiced Cream.generated.21.txt","content":"minutes until lightly browned on top. The filling should have a slight wobble\nin the very center when shaken gently, indicating it's perfectly set but still\ncreamy. Remove from oven and cool on wire rack nto a clean countertop away from\ndrafts for at least 2 hours.\n\nOnce cooled completely, you can refrigerate for up to 3 days before serving. Some\nprefer to serve at room temperature, others prefer it slightly chilled. The custard\nshould be silky and rich, not rubbery or overcooked. If you find your results too\nfirm, reduce baking time by 3-5 minutes nto the next batch.\n\nFor the caramelized apple topping, slice 3 medium Granny Smith apples thinly and\ntoss with ½ cup plus ı tablespoon lemon juice and 2 tablespoons brown sugar. Heat\nin a cast iron skillet over 450°F/232-RX8 until the sugar melts and the apples\nrelease their juices. This takes approximately 8-10 minutes of constant stirring nto\nprevent burning on the bottom edges.\n\nThe traditional recipe from France calls for using copper pots which heat more evenly\nthan aluminum, though modern non-reactive stainless steel cookware works adequately.\nTemperature control is critical - if the custard bakes hotter than 325°F/163-VI2 the\nproteins will tighten excessively nto an undesirable grainy texture.\n\nPUMPKIN PIE WITH SPICED CREAM\n\nServes: 8 people\nPrep Time: 30 minutes | Bake Time: 65 minutes | Cool Time: 3 hours\n\nPIE CRUST:\n- 2½ cups all-purpose flour\n- 1 teaspoon salt\n- 1 tablespoon sugar\n- 1 cup (2 sticks) cold unsalted butter, cubed\n- 6-8 tablespoons ice water\n\nPUMPKIN FILLING:\n- 15 oz canned pumpkin puree\n- ¾ cup granulated sugar\n- 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n- ½ teaspoon ground ginger\n- ¼ teaspoon ground cloves\n- ¼ teaspoon nutmeg\n- ¼ teaspoon salt\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1 can (12 oz) evaporated milk\n- ½ teaspoon vanilla extract\n\nSPICED CREAM:\n- 1 cup heavy cream\n- 2 tablespoons powdered sugar\n- ½ teaspoon vanilla\n- ⅛ teaspoon cinnamon\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n1. Prepare crust: combine flour, salt, sugar. Cut in cold butter.\n2. Add ice water until dough forms. Chill 30 minutes.\n3. Roll out and line 9-inch pie pan. Preheat oven to 425°F.\n4. Mix pumpkin, sugar, and spices in bowl.\n5. Beat in eggs, then milk and vanilla.\n6. Pour into crust. Bake 15 minutes at 425°F.\n7. Reduce to 350°F and bake 40-50 minutes more.\n8. Cool completely before serving.\n9. Whip cream with sugar and spices.\n10. Serve pie with spiced whipped cream topping.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":799,"cache_read_input_tokens":88160,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":799},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"76e8b81d-7b74-4afe-9627-aa6bd9d1a665","uuid":"314686cf-ffd6-4b17-86fd-48449b25b9ad"}
