{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Cs4rAYRxVCJ9sSvayXtQAH","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Pumpkin Pie with Spiced Cream.generated.21.txt has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"76e8b81d-7b74-4afe-9627-aa6bd9d1a665","uuid":"11ebb28e-58ef-45d2-9d43-26e17be7b1c7","tool_use_result":{"type":"update","filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Pumpkin Pie with Spiced Cream.generated.21.txt","content":"minutes until lightly browned on top. The filling should have a slight wobble\nin the very center when shaken gently, indicating it's perfectly set but still\ncreamy. Remove from oven and cool on wire rack nto a clean countertop away from\ndrafts for at least 2 hours.\n\nOnce cooled completely, you can refrigerate for up to 3 days before serving. Some\nprefer to serve at room temperature, others prefer it slightly chilled. The custard\nshould be silky and rich, not rubbery or overcooked. If you find your results too\nfirm, reduce baking time by 3-5 minutes nto the next batch.\n\nFor the caramelized apple topping, slice 3 medium Granny Smith apples thinly and\ntoss with ½ cup plus ı tablespoon lemon juice and 2 tablespoons brown sugar. Heat\nin a cast iron skillet over 450°F/232-RX8 until the sugar melts and the apples\nrelease their juices. This takes approximately 8-10 minutes of constant stirring nto\nprevent burning on the bottom edges.\n\nThe traditional recipe from France calls for using copper pots which heat more evenly\nthan aluminum, though modern non-reactive stainless steel cookware works adequately.\nTemperature control is critical - if the custard bakes hotter than 325°F/163-VI2 the\nproteins will tighten excessively nto an undesirable grainy texture.\n\nPUMPKIN PIE WITH SPICED CREAM\n\nServes: 8 people\nPrep Time: 30 minutes | Bake Time: 65 minutes | Cool Time: 3 hours\n\nPIE CRUST:\n- 2½ cups all-purpose flour\n- 1 teaspoon salt\n- 1 tablespoon sugar\n- 1 cup (2 sticks) cold unsalted butter, cubed\n- 6-8 tablespoons ice water\n\nPUMPKIN FILLING:\n- 15 oz canned pumpkin puree\n- ¾ cup granulated sugar\n- 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n- ½ teaspoon ground ginger\n- ¼ teaspoon ground cloves\n- ¼ teaspoon nutmeg\n- ¼ teaspoon salt\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1 can (12 oz) evaporated milk\n- ½ teaspoon vanilla extract\n\nSPICED CREAM:\n- 1 cup heavy cream\n- 2 tablespoons powdered sugar\n- ½ teaspoon vanilla\n- ⅛ teaspoon cinnamon\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n1. Prepare crust: combine flour, salt, sugar. Cut in cold butter.\n2. Add ice water until dough forms. Chill 30 minutes.\n3. Roll out and line 9-inch pie pan. Preheat oven to 425°F.\n4. Mix pumpkin, sugar, and spices in bowl.\n5. Beat in eggs, then milk and vanilla.\n6. Pour into crust. Bake 15 minutes at 425°F.\n7. Reduce to 350°F and bake 40-50 minutes more.\n8. Cool completely before serving.\n9. Whip cream with sugar and spices.\n10. Serve pie with spiced whipped cream topping.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":20,"newStart":1,"newLines":38,"lines":["-PUMPKIN","-PIE","-WITH SPICED","-CREAM","+minutes until lightly browned on top. The filling should have a slight wobble","+in the very center when shaken gently, indicating it's perfectly set but still","+creamy. Remove from oven and cool on wire rack nto a clean countertop away from","+drafts for at least 2 hours."," ","-American fall classic featuring roasted pumpkin puree in a flaky pie crust.","+Once cooled completely, you can refrigerate for up to 3 days before serving. Some","+prefer to serve at room temperature, others prefer it slightly chilled. The custard","+should be silky and rich, not rubbery or overcooked. If you find your results too","+firm, reduce baking time by 3-5 minutes nto the next batch."," ","-CRUST INGREDIENTS:","+For the caramelized apple topping, slice 3 medium Granny Smith apples thinly and","+toss with ½ cup plus ı tablespoon lemon juice and 2 tablespoons brown sugar. Heat","+in a cast iron skillet over 450°F/232-RX8 until the sugar melts and the apples","+release their juices. This takes approximately 8-10 minutes of constant stirring nto","+prevent burning on the bottom edges.","+","+The traditional recipe from France calls for using copper pots which heat more evenly","+than aluminum, though modern non-reactive stainless steel cookware works adequately.","+Temperature control is critical - if the custard bakes hotter than 325°F/163-VI2 the","+proteins will tighten excessively nto an undesirable grainy texture.","+","+PUMPKIN PIE WITH SPICED CREAM","+","+Serves: 8 people","+Prep Time: 30 minutes | Bake Time: 65 minutes | Cool Time: 3 hours","+","+PIE CRUST:"," - 2½ cups all-purpose flour"," - 1 teaspoon salt"," - 1 tablespoon sugar"," - 1 cup (2 sticks) cold unsalted butter, cubed"," - 6-8 tablespoons ice water","-- 1 egg (for egg wash)"," ","-FILLING INGREDIENTS:","-- 15 oz canned pumpkin puree (or fresh roasted)","+PUMPKIN FILLING:","+- 15 oz canned pumpkin puree"," - ¾ cup granulated sugar"," - 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon"," - ½ teaspoon ground ginger"]},{"oldStart":25,"oldLines":28,"newStart":43,"newLines":20,"lines":[" - 1 can (12 oz) evaporated milk"," - ½ teaspoon vanilla extract"," ","-SPICED CREAM TOPPING:","+SPICED CREAM:"," - 1 cup heavy cream"," - 2 tablespoons powdered sugar","-- ½ teaspoon vanilla extract","+- ½ teaspoon vanilla"," - ⅛ teaspoon cinnamon","-- Pinch of nutmeg"," "," INSTRUCTIONS:","-1. Make crust: Mix flour, salt, and sugar in bowl.","-2. Cut in cold butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.","-3. Add ice water, one tablespoon at a time, until dough just comes together.","-4. Form into disk, wrap in plastic, refrigerate 30 minutes.","-5. Roll out dough and line 9-inch pie pan. Trim overhang.","-6. Preheat oven to 425°F (218°C).","-7. For filling: Whisk together pumpkin, sugar, and spices.","-8. Beat in eggs, then evaporated milk and vanilla.","-9. Pour filling into crust.","-10. Bake at 425°F for 15 minutes, then reduce to 350°F (177°C).","-11. Bake additional 40-50 minutes until knife inserted near center comes out clean.","-12. Cool on wire rack.","-13. For topping: Whip cream with sugar, vanilla, and spices until stiff peaks form.","-14. Serve pie warm or at room temperature with spiced whipped cream.","-","-SERVES: 8 people","-PREP TIME: 20 minutes | BAKE TIME: 60 minutes","+1. Prepare crust: combine flour, salt, sugar. Cut in cold butter.","+2. Add ice water until dough forms. Chill 30 minutes.","+3. Roll out and line 9-inch pie pan. Preheat oven to 425°F.","+4. Mix pumpkin, sugar, and spices in bowl.","+5. Beat in eggs, then milk and vanilla.","+6. Pour into crust. Bake 15 minutes at 425°F.","+7. Reduce to 350°F and bake 40-50 minutes more.","+8. Cool completely before serving.","+9. Whip cream with sugar and spices.","+10. Serve pie with spiced whipped cream topping."]}],"originalFile":"PUMPKIN\nPIE\nWITH SPICED\nCREAM\n\nAmerican fall classic featuring roasted pumpkin puree in a flaky pie crust.\n\nCRUST INGREDIENTS:\n- 2½ cups all-purpose flour\n- 1 teaspoon salt\n- 1 tablespoon sugar\n- 1 cup (2 sticks) cold unsalted butter, cubed\n- 6-8 tablespoons ice water\n- 1 egg (for egg wash)\n\nFILLING INGREDIENTS:\n- 15 oz canned pumpkin puree (or fresh roasted)\n- ¾ cup granulated sugar\n- 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon\n- ½ teaspoon ground ginger\n- ¼ teaspoon ground cloves\n- ¼ teaspoon nutmeg\n- ¼ teaspoon salt\n- 2 large eggs\n- 1 can (12 oz) evaporated milk\n- ½ teaspoon vanilla extract\n\nSPICED CREAM TOPPING:\n- 1 cup heavy cream\n- 2 tablespoons powdered sugar\n- ½ teaspoon vanilla extract\n- ⅛ teaspoon cinnamon\n- Pinch of nutmeg\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n1. Make crust: Mix flour, salt, and sugar in bowl.\n2. Cut in cold butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.\n3. Add ice water, one tablespoon at a time, until dough just comes together.\n4. Form into disk, wrap in plastic, refrigerate 30 minutes.\n5. Roll out dough and line 9-inch pie pan. Trim overhang.\n6. Preheat oven to 425°F (218°C).\n7. For filling: Whisk together pumpkin, sugar, and spices.\n8. Beat in eggs, then evaporated milk and vanilla.\n9. Pour filling into crust.\n10. Bake at 425°F for 15 minutes, then reduce to 350°F (177°C).\n11. Bake additional 40-50 minutes until knife inserted near center comes out clean.\n12. Cool on wire rack.\n13. For topping: Whip cream with sugar, vanilla, and spices until stiff peaks form.\n14. Serve pie warm or at room temperature with spiced whipped cream.\n\nSERVES: 8 people\nPREP TIME: 20 minutes | BAKE TIME: 60 minutes\n"}}
